  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community Managed Women&#x2019;s Rights Advocacy Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a result of negative socio-cultural beliefs and practices, women in Chitipa district in the Karonga Diocese of Malawi are often restricted from enjoying some of their rights. Women are regarded as inferior to their male counter-parts, and most of them become victims of sexual and physical abuse. Access to education by girls is limited as compared to their male counterparts, and many girls are forced into early marriages, resulting in a large number of teenage mothers. This project seeks to further improve the right of woman and girls in St Ignatius Parish, Malawi.

Since 2012, CAFOD has supported Karonga Diocese, through its Justice and Peace Desk to implement a &#x201C;Securing the Rights of women and Girls&#x201D; project. The project managed to build capacity of local structures to deal with cultural practices that violate the rights of women and girls. Through the project, Karonga Diocese created and trained Women&#x2019;s Rights Groups, which were responsible for raising awareness on cultural/traditional practises that violate rights of both women and girls, and referring cases of violation to the relevant authorities. The proposed project is therefore scaling up the work that Karonga Diocese has done through the &quot;Securing the Rights of women and Girls&#x201D; project.</narrative>
  </description>
